The paper deals with algorithms for approximating semi-matchings in bipartite graphs, which is a problem in graph theory and combinatorial optimization. The focus is on communication complexity and streaming complexity, which are both areas of theoretical computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) in the context of communication protocols, and computational geometry (cs.CG) in the context of bipartite graphs.
